article.headline: New Mexico State 73, Boise State 69
article.story: BOISE, Idaho (AP) -- Elijah Ingram scored 15 points and Hatila Passos added 13 points and 12 rebounds as New Mexico State moved its winning streak to 13 games by defeating Boise State 73-69 on Saturday. The Aggies (14-3, 4-0 Western Athletic Conference) withstood a furious comeback by the Broncos by hitting nine of their last 10 free throws. Reggie Larry scored 19 points and had eight rebounds for the Broncos (8-7, 2-2 WAC), who saw their seven-game home winning streak snapped. The Broncos never led and trailed by as many as 15 points early in the second half but pulled to within a point at 68-67 on Coby Karl's two free throws with 25.9 seconds left. But the Broncos were forced to foul, and Ingram made two free throws and, after a missed 3-pointer by the Broncos' Eric Lane, Justin Hawkins added two more free throws for the Aggies to make it 72-67 with 10.7 seconds left. Lane was given an open path for a layup and Ingram made one of two free throws with 3.1 seconds left for the final score. The Aggies outrebounded the Broncos 42-32, and had 18 offensive rebounds to Boise State's nine. New Mexico State threatened to blow the game open in the first half with a combination of hot shooting and offensive rebounds while the Broncos struggled for points. The Broncos couldn't stop New Mexico State's Tyron Nelson in the first half. He worked his way to the basket consistently to score 8 points in a 14-8 run that put New Mexico State ahead 31-16 with about seven minutes left in the half. But the Broncos made an 8-0 run, capped by Matt Bauscher's offensive rebound and layup, to close out the half trailing 36-30. The two teams each made about 44 percent of their shots, but the Aggies took 58 shots to the Broncos' 50.
